# Spec 011 — Commute-Data Accuracy: Routed Estimates, Local Time, Honest Framing

Status: Draft
Owner: <you>
Related: 003-commute-depth (supersedes its Matrix-API deferral),
004-backend-hardening (rate limit / budget / geofence reused),
009-zip-explorer (the detail panel this feeds)

## Overview

Spot checks show the commute layer can materially understate real rush-hour
drives (Tukwila→Gig Harbor reads as ≤60 min; reality is 60–120). Three causes:
Mapbox isochrones model *typical* (median-ish) traffic and are least accurate
at the 60-minute cap fringe; the panel's reach line judges a ZIP by its
centroid against a generalized polygon; and the morning home→work direction —
often the worst — is unmodeled (isochrones only radiate outward from work).
Separately, departure dates are rolled on a hardcoded Pacific clock for all
51 states. This spec adds true point-to-point routed estimates (Mapbox
Directions API) per selected ZIP in both directions, fixes the timezone
handling, and reframes all commute copy as typical-traffic estimates.

## Context

- Mapbox interprets a naive `depart_at` as local time at the ORIGIN, so the
  scenario hours are already correct nationally. The `METRO_TZ` bug is about
  date-rolling: an Eastern-time user between 5–8 PM local gets a `depart_at`
  already in the past (undocumented upstream behavior), and weekday rolls can
  pin wrong dates. AK/HI windows are larger.
- The Directions API supports `depart_at` with `driving-traffic` (GA — unlike
  the Matrix API, whose beta 422s forced spec 003 to defer per-ZIP times).
  One routed call per direction; `routes[0].duration` is traffic-predicted.
- All hardening from 004 applies unchanged: per-IP rate limit, daily upstream
  budget, ~500 m snapping, coverage geofence, in-process TTL caches.

## Requirements

- **R1 — Local-time scenarios.** Isochrone departure dates are computed in
  the work location's local timezone via a state→IANA map (region resolved by
  containing bbox, ties by distance to center; longitude-derived fixed-offset
  fallback off-coverage). `METRO_TZ` is removed. Split states use their
  dominant zone (documented in the mapping: TX→Chicago, FL/MI/IN/KY→New_York,
  ID→Boise, AZ→Phoenix, AK→Anchorage, HI→Honolulu, …).
- **R2 — Point-to-point commute estimates.** `GET /api/commute` with
  validated `from_lat/from_lon` (home) and `to_lat/to_lon` (work) returns
  `am_minutes` (home→work, departing next weekday 08:00 home-local) and
  `pm_minutes` (work→home, departing 17:30 work-local) from Mapbox Directions
  `driving-traffic` + `depart_at`, plus the departure labels.
- **R3 — Panel display.** Selecting a ZIP shows "Drive to work: ~52 min
  (Mon 8:00 AM)" and "Drive home: ~64 min (Mon 5:30 PM)" leading the detail
  panel's context block; the band-membership line follows, reworded.
- **R4 — Honest framing.** Commute copy everywhere says *typical* traffic;
  the band line adds "bad days run longer"; routed estimates name their
  departure time.
- **R5 — Safety preserved.** Token server-side only, never in responses,
  errors, or logs (001 R5). Each uncached estimate reserves 2 upstream calls
  via the daily budget (004 R3); the endpoint is rate-limited (004 R1); both
  endpoints geofenced to covered regions; both coordinates snapped to the
  500 m grid before cache key and upstream call; results (including
  no-route) cached 24 h; a ~250 mi straight-line guard rejects non-commute
  pairs with 422.
- **R6 — Graceful degradation.** Missing token, exhausted budget, or
  upstream failure → 503; no drivable route → 404. The frontend treats all
  of these as "no estimate lines" (best-effort, no toast); the rest of the
  panel is unaffected. No fixture mode for this endpoint.

## Non-functional / Constraints

- No new dependencies (zoneinfo + tzdata are already shipped).
- Cost: 2 Directions calls per uncached (ZIP, work) pair — bounded by the
  existing `MAPBOX_DAILY_CALL_BUDGET` and well inside the 100k/month free
  tier at current traffic.
- Frontend fetch is debounced so pin-dragging with an open panel cannot
  burst-spend the rate limit.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] With a live token, work pin near Tukwila + a Gig Harbor ZIP selected:
      the routed AM/PM numbers land in the realistic 60–120 min range — no
      longer implied to be ≤60 by band membership alone.
- [ ] A work pin in the Eastern time zone produces `depart_at` dates that
      are in the future in Eastern time, evening requests included.
- [ ] Two ZIP centroids <500 m apart produce one upstream pair (snap+cache);
      re-selecting the same ZIP spends nothing.
- [ ] Budget exhausted / token absent / no route degrade exactly per R6 with
      the token absent from every response and the browser Network tab.
- [ ] All commute copy reads as typical-traffic estimates with departure
      times named; the band line includes "bad days run longer".
- [ ] `pytest` and `npm run test` pass with the new tz, commute, and panel
      tests.

## Out of Scope (explicit)

- Percentile/pessimistic traffic (requires a different provider).
- Reverse isochrones; transit/walk/cycle modes; user-chosen departure times.
- Matrix-API whole-map per-ZIP coloring (call volume; remains deferred).

